

For a standard install, execute : 
    - configure --prefix=<install rep> --with-mpi=<rep mpi> CC=<C ompiler>  CXX=<C++ compiler> FC=<fortran compiler>
    - make
    - make install

CC, CCX or FC accept MPI compiler wrapper (mpicc, ...). In this case, do not use '--with-mpi' option.

To see all configure options, execute 'configure --help'

To compile and execute tests, execute :
    - make
    - make install
    - make check NP=<number of processus (default 2)> MPI_EXEC=<mpi launcher (default mpiexec)> MPI_NP=<argument before the number of processus (default -np)>

To use valgrind, add VALGRIND=<path> option
To execute only few tests, define TESTS option




 
